venue.name: Sushi Mori (ซูชิ โมริ)

tip.text: It is still as quaint as ever though prices can be steep. Come for the lunch sets and cream teas which are worth the value.
The idea of mixing Japanese with Italian/Western is good but they tend to be v heavy handed in the chilli and/or pepper seasoning. This was esp so for the hotate mentai pasta and spicy vongole soup
The food is done thoughtfully to give justice to its freshness. The grilled wagyu has a crisp surface yet tender centre. You really get good value, esp if you hold a Feed at Raffles card.

tip.text: One comes to Restaurant Andrew to learn and explore flavours. Enjoy the ~2 hour journey. It is certainly fruitful, peppered with a few surprises. Bon Appétit!
